from scipy import ndimage
import numpy as np
img=np.zeros((512,512,20))
for n in range(0,20):
    s=n+1
    filePath = 'D:/liver_mask_pd/'+str(s)+'_predict.png'
    imgslice = cv2.imread(filePath)
    imgslice = imgslice[:,:,0]/255
    imgslice=ndimage.binary_fill_holes(imgslice).astype(int)
    img[:,:,n]=imgslice
    plt.imshow(imgslice,cmap='gray')
    plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from matplotlib.patches import Circle
dif=np.zeros((20,20))
for slice in range(0,20):
    liverslice=liver[:,:,slice]
    pdffpixel=np.nonzero(liverslice)
    pdffp=np.vstack(pdffpixel)
    pdffp=np.transpose(pdffp)
    pdffliver=liverslice[np.nonzero(liverslice)]
    pdmean=np.mean(ff[slice])
    print('The mean of PDFF:',pdmean)
    #Kernel = np.ones((3, 3))
    print(pdffpixel)
#liver10[160:357,:]
    d=pdmean
    autof=np.ones((10000,2))
    pm=np.ones((10000))
    pdroi=np.ones((10000))
    s=0
    for i in range(0,10000):
        rand_arr = np.arange(pdffp.shape[0])
        np.random.shuffle(rand_arr)
        pdffpoint=pdffp[rand_arr[0]]
        kernel=liverslice[pdffpoint[1]-2:pdffpoint[1]+3,pdffpoint[0]-2:pdffpoint[0]+3]
    #for i in range(0,5):
    #    for j in range(0,5):
    #        print(row_rand_array[0]-1+i,col_rand_array[0]-1+j)
        pdffroi=np.mean(kernel)
    #print(pdffroi)
        pm[i]=pdmean
        pdroi[i]=pdffroi
        diff=abs(pdmean-pdffroi)
    #d=diff
        if diff<d:
            d=diff
            arrpixel=(pdffpoint[1],pdffpoint[0])
            x = arrpixel[0]
            y = arrpixel[1]
            autof[i]=[x,y]
            print('The mean of ROI PDFF:',pdffroi)
            print('The difference of PDFF:',d)
            print('The accuarcy:',100-d)
            dif[slice,s]=diff
            s=s+1
    x=autof[:,0]
    y=autof[:,1]
    fig,ax = plt.subplots(1)
    ax.set_aspect('equal')

# Show the image
    ax.imshow(liverslice,cmap='gray',vmax=100,vmin=0)
    for xx,yy in zip(x,y):
        circ = Circle((xx,yy),3,fill = False,color='red')
        ax.add_patch(circ)
    # Show the image
    plt.show()
